{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583696","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583696"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:25:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:25:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12554"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12554","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12554"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5053"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"44220"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5053","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5053"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12554"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29169"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"15"},{"type":"tags","id":"39"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"73"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"486"},{"type":"tags","id":"1845"},{"type":"tags","id":"4183"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4945"},{"type":"tags","id":"10758"},{"type":"tags","id":"10762"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8405"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8515"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11298"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"44220","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/44220"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30-year-old male presents with a history of recurrent episodes of gross haematuria and proteinuria. His father has a history of end-stage renal disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, his blood pressure was 140/90 and pulse rate of 140/min.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHis kidney biopsy shows diffuse mesangial proliferation with IgA deposits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following HLA serotypes might predispose to his condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["HLA-DR3","HLA-DR4","HLA-B27","HLA-DQ2","HLA-DQ8"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most commonly associated HLA serotype with IgA nephropathy is\u003Cstrong\u003E HLA-DR3.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIgA nephropathy is a common form of glomerulonephritis caused by the deposition of IgA immunoglobulins in the glomerular basement membrane. Immune-mediated damage to the basement membrane results in haematuria and renal insufficiency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-DR4\u003C/strong\u003E has been found to be associated with autoimmune diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis, but there is no strong association with IGA nephropathy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-B27\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with certain inflammatory conditions such as ankylosing spondylitis, but there is no known association with IGA nephropathy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-DQ2 \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-DQ8\u003C/strong\u003E are associated with celiac disease, but there is no known association with IGA nephropathy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The serotype most associated with IgA nephropathy is HLA-DR3."],"references":["Rawla P, Limaiem F, Hashmi MF. IgA Nephropathy. [Updated 2022 Nov 27]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan-."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29169"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12554"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29169","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/29169"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-04-09T21:19:56+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-04-09T21:19:56+0